{"type":"message","id":"4c387d73","parentId":"878b460a","timestamp":"2026-02-15T17:44:00.064Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sun 2026-02-15 19:43 GMT+2] OPERATION: OODA LOOP & POLYGLOT FOUNDATION.\n\n1.  **Sync Gap (The Watchdog Test):**\n    *   *Act:* `git push origin dev`\n    *   *Observe:* If `rejected` (non-fast-forward):\n        *   `git pull --rebase origin dev`\n        *   *Decide:* If conflicts in `requirements.txt` -> Accept LOCAL (ours is cleaner).\n        *   `git push origin dev`\n    *   *Goal:* Console output MUST say \"Everything up-to-date\" or \"Pushed\".\n\n2.  **DevOps 2.0 (Pre-commit):**\n    *   *Act:* Create `.pre-commit-config.yaml` (trailing-whitespace, flake8, shellcheck).\n    *   *Act:* `pip install pre-commit && pre-commit install`.\n    *   *Observe:* Check for \"pre-commit installed at .git/hooks/pre-commit\".\n\n3.  **Redis Upgrade (Smart Memory):**\n    *   *Act:* Edit `docker-compose.yml`. Replace `redis:alpine` with `redis/redis-stack-server:latest`.\n\n4.  **Rust Foundation (PyO3):**\n    *   *Act:* Create `src/rust_core/Cargo.toml`.\n    *   *Act:* Create `src/rust_core/src/lib.rs` (Stub).\n    *   *Observe:* Check if `cargo` exists. If not, log \"Rust missing, adding to Dockerfile\".\n\n5.  **Output:**\n    *   Push Log (Real console output).\n    *   Pre-commit installation status.\n    *   Redis image verification.\n    *   Rust readiness report."}],"timestamp":1771177440062}}
{"type":"message","id":"fed5fed2","parentId":"4c387d73","timestamp":"2026-02-15T17:44:21.989Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Refining the Approach**\n\nI'm currently focused on the Git synchronization aspect. I need to make sure I can seamlessly manage rebasing and potential conflicts that might arise during the Git push. My next step will be working on pre-commit hooks.\n\n\n**Evaluating Git Strategy**\n\nI've just been looking at the basic workflow for the Git synchronization. I am now planning to deal with conflicts in `requirements.txt` specifically. The strategy is to handle rebasing and keep local changes.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1771177461184_20","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"git push origin dev"},"thoughtSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771177461306_21","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"repos:\n  - repo: https://github.com/pre-commit/pre-commit-hooks\n    rev: v4.4.0\n    hooks:\n      - id: trailing-whitespace\n      - id: end-of-file-fixer\n      - id: check-yaml\n      - id: check-added-large-files\n  - repo: https://github.com/pycqa/flake8\n    rev: 6.0.0\n    hooks:\n      - id: flake8\n  - repo: https://github.com/koalaman/shellcheck-precommit\n    rev: v0.9.0\n    hooks:\n      - id: shellcheck\n","file_path":".pre-commit-config.yaml"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1771177461415_22","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"pip install pre-commit && pre-commit install"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771177461791_23","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"docker-compose.yml"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771177461791_24","name":"write","arguments":{"file_path":"src/rust_core/Cargo.toml","content":"[package]\nname = \"rust_core\"\nversion = \"0.1.0\"\nedition = \"2021\"\n\n[lib]\nname = \"rust_core\"\ncrate-type = [\"cdylib\"]\n\n[dependencies]\npyo3 = { version = \"0.19.0\", features = [\"extension-module\"] }\n"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771177461792_25","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"use pyo3::prelude::*;\n\n/// Formats the sum of two numbers as string.\n#[pyfunction]\nfn sum_as_string(a: usize, b: usize) -> PyResult<String> {\n    Ok((a + b).to_string())\n}\n\n/// A Python module implemented in Rust.\n#[pymodule]\nfn rust_core(_py: Python, m: &PyModule) -> PyResult<()> {\n    m.add_function(wrap_pyfunction!(sum_as_string, m)?)?;\n    Ok(())\n}\n","file_path":"src/rust_core/src/lib.rs"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1771177461866_26","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cargo --version"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1771177461986_27","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"git status"}}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":4869,"output":553,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":5422,"cost":{"input":0.009738,"output":0.006636,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.016374}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771177440063}}
