{"type":"message","id":"7732118d","parentId":"003d5523","timestamp":"2026-02-15T17:44:50.809Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Reviewing Initial Findings**\n\nI'm analyzing the outputs from the previous tool executions. The initial git push command completed without changes, indicating the codebase is up-to-date on the remote dev branch. I am now proceeding to review the pre-commit configuration.\n\n\n**Interpreting Commands & Results**\n\nI'm interpreting the outcomes of the prior tool executions, focusing on the git sync and pre-commit setup. The `git push` result was as expected. I need to handle the pre-commit install; the PowerShell issue with the `&&` operator is noted. I'll execute the commands separately to ensure stability. Also, I need to add Redis service because it is missing.\n\n\n**Executing Subsequent Tasks**\n\nNow, I'm working through the revised plan. First, I'll execute the pre-commit installation commands sequentially as discussed earlier, so `pip install pre-commit` then `pre-commit install`. Next, I'll update the `docker-compose.yml` to include the Redis service. After that, I will read the `Dockerfile` to decide how best to include the Rust installation and modify it. Finally, I'll prepare a comprehensive report summarizing all performed tasks and their results.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1771177490250_28","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"pip install pre-commit"},"thoughtSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1771177490759_29","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"pre-commit install"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771177490759_30","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"Dockerfile"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"edit_1771177490809_31","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"docker-compose.yml","newText":"  watchtower:\n    image: containrrr/watchtower\n    container_name: dmarket-watchtower\n    volumes:\n      - /var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock\n    command: --interval 360